  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "Admission to the Computer Science Engineering (CSE) program at VIT Chennai is competitive and depends on several factors, including your performance in the VIT Engineering Entrance Examination (VITEEE) and the overall applicant pool for the year. Generally, CSE tends to have higher cut-offs due to its popularity.\n\nIn recent years, the cut-off marks for CSE have typically ranged higher than 70, often requiring scores in the 80s or above to secure a seat. However, exact cut-off scores can vary each year based on the number of applicants, their performance, and the specific admissions policies of the university.\n\nTo increase your chances of admission, it\u2019s advisable to aim for a higher score. Additionally, you can check the official VIT website or contact their admissions office for the most current information regarding cut-offs and admission criteria for the specific year you're applying to.",
